<plot>Using newsreel footage, this Sportscope entry chronicles the race toward running's four-minute mile, highlighting several important contests. It starts in the 1920's, when Finland's 'Paavo Nurmi' (qv) set the record for the distance at 4 minutes 10.4 seconds. It continues through 'Roger Bannister' (qv)'s first run under 4 minutes in 1954, and ends in spring 1956, when Australia's 'Joe Bailey (III)' (qv) became the first to break 4 minutes on US soil.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?201543</url></doc>
